Future Diary should be clear to any potential viewer that it is yet another one of\
          \
        those Battle Royale-style story, in which there will be a bunch of high school kids and throw them into a situation where they have to pit off against one another (alright, I am oversimplification of things in Future Diary, but you get the idea). Such story should not be foreign to most people, seeing the popularity of similar plot in popular western franchise such as the Hunger Games, as well as in Japan, such as the Zero Escape or Fate franchise. Many people was sold on the idea that Future Diary is going to be a thought-provoking psychological thriller that blows their mind, only to have all their expectation thrown out, getting a seemingly incomprehensible mess that was far from what they actually expected. It is very much due to this that many viewers develop a distaste for Future Diary. \
Many people have used the term 'trainwreck' to describe the final outcome of this show, but I personally think that that is too demeaning of a term to be used on Future Diary. Simply said, the sheer craziness of Future Diary can't just be contained within a train (or 2 or 10 or 10,000 for that matter). Future Diary may be an incoherent mess, totally illogical, with the story flowing through by any means but with a constant flow. If the thought of the aforementioned turns you off, then Future Diary is definitely not a show for you. And there really isn't much point for you in continuing this review. Of course unless you are interested in knowing why Future Diary is an art, then welcome on-board the train. You still with me? Good, let me convince you why this mess is absolutely wonderful (Allow me to articulate this clearly, this review is not a piece of satire).\
Let me first talk about what I deemed as one of the best part of the story: the twist, oh the plot twist, hail them. The \"deus ex machina\" (the plot device, not the character) present in this show is often subjected to multiple criticisms by critics and reviewers alike. Not only do the twists seems absolutely nonsensical and bonkers at times, they only further elevate the amount of questioning in the show. Future Diary is absurd and ludicrous to the core, do not expect good logical flow in the story. This again, is what makes Future Diary so amazing: the roller coaster ride of events after events to an unthinkable extent, logic simply does not exist.\
Allow me to put it this way: both the original mangaka (Sakae Esuno-sensei) and the staff are an irresponsible bunch. They couldn't care for the logic in this show (if they even care for it in the first place). However, it is also precisely due to this that Future Diary could be successful in the first place. The people working on this show knows what Future Diary lacks (logic) and at the same time is clear of its strength (the absurdity). The ridiculous pacing turns away most of the viewers, but this perhaps really just highlighted the greatness of this show. It just gives you this crazy adrenaline pump to continue watching. It spends little to absolutely no time to explaining the illogical stuffs (For a couple of reasons, such as too many of them, inability to explain, or as I see it, unnecessary in this crazy show) and will just let the next major event before the viewer can even take a breather. This is why, the very essence, the heart, the core, of Future Diary would be these insane and out-of-mind plot points. You expect it to come, it had being foreshadowed all the way from the beginning, you are waiting for it to happen, yet you just could not pinpoint what exactly and when exactly it will occur, and you will get completely overwhelmed by it why it comes (in both a good or bad way). \
The following point will unfortunately incorporate my arguments made for the story relatively closely, and that is the characters in the show. Once again, if you are looking for well fleshed-out characters in this show, sorry but there really isn't any. While most of the characters do get a backstory explaining their course of action (of course, the stories being totally illogical), their presence is merely a fodder for the story to progress, and not as a being that drives a story forward. If there were any characters that I might want to focus on, that would be the main characters Yukiteru (Yuki for the rest of the review) and Yuno. Yuki is the wimpy, ain't-getting-anything-done protagonist that just unfortunately generate lots of hate among the viewers. From his character design of wearing a abnormal hat to his every action in the show, it just screams \"weak\". It is no doubt irritating to see the main protagonist not doing anything. Personally, while I am no fan of him, the hate generated due to him seems quite unreasonable (Oh my, I'm talking about reasons in Future Diary). Come on guys, he's a kid thrown into crazy stuff that he could not even imagine, forcing him into all these crazy stuff just seemed all the more nonsensical (now I'm talking \"sense\", welp!). This is more so ridiculous in the presence of the all-powerful girlfriend, Yuno. Yuno is totally bonkers, crazy, because as if I need to reiterate that. Disturbing staring of the eyes and pink hair in the air every time she swings her axe, she is probably the poster image for a psychopath in anime. However, if there were any character, it was her that keeps the show going. Her absurd antics to win Yuki over and have him accept her, the preposterous acts against the other diary holders, it was almost entertainment at its finest. And for her to keep this momentum going... she is definitely not any great protagonist by any means, but there will be no doubt in her being one of the most memorable one. Now, you combine the wimpy kid and the dominating queen, a weird and illogical combination, but it is this dynamics that drive the show and further heightens the general atmosphere. \
Regarding stuffs such as animation and sound, I really doubt that there is much to talk about. I do want to praise the first opening theme (\"Kuusou Mesorogiwi\" by Yousei Teikoku) for the mysterious-chant at the start of the song to hype the viewer up each time, as well as the crazy amount of foreshadowing in the sequence. The rest of the theme songs and decent though nothing especially great. The voice acting, well, having the voice actors shouting and screaming around doing what they usually don't is always entertaining. Animation, by Studio Asread, is nothing amazing though nothing much to criticise on as well. Fight sequence are generally well-animated well the more \"daily\" scenes have a lower animation quality, which I personally do not mind and has no qualm with.\
I genuinely enjoys Future Diary. If I had any reason for such, here is my hypothesis (feel free to skip it): The fruit of wisdom had let mankind gain the ability to question, and thus quench the thirst of knowledge. Future Diary, (un)fortunately, leaves the viewer with an insurmountable number of questions, completely perplexed at what they had seen. But does it matter? I do not think so. While logical thought process is important, humans still could not escape the control of emotion, the illogical side of every human being. Perhaps, really, nothing could top Future Diary in this domain. Anything can happen. The madness and lunacy just snowballs throughout the whole show without a stop. It is a spot-on hit on the illogical side of human, something that targets the hysteria and psychopathic side of mankind. You know that something stupid is going to happen, yet you will (not) advance. You want to see how Future Diary's absurdity can top itself every single episode. It is this pulpiness and the juiciness in Future Diary that just make it more so interesting. This is not something that an institution which favours logical thinking will be pleased with. Future Diary really is something that appeals to the more inhumane side of human, the illogical and overly-emotional aspect. To phrase it in another way, Future Diary is not (supposed to be) a critic's favourite. If you are only going to favour the logical aspect of the show, something that is absolutely missing in Future Diary, then it is anything but hard for one to slap a 4/10 or 3/10 onto this show and criticise every single plot point in this show. However, Future Diary is those show that should be judged by upon anything but the logical flow of thoughts in the show (because it does not exist). If anything, Future Diary appeals to that emotional and illogical side of human. If anyone is going to ask me why didn't I rate Future Diary a 10/10, I would pretty much just answer that there is this little bit of sanity and logical flow left in me that simply could not ignore the flaws in Future Diary (Come on now, what I am trying to say is not that people who criticise this show are emotionless creatures and that everyone that gives this show a 10/10 is a psychopath). I am in the opinion that Future Diary is no doubt one of the more controversial and subjective show that anyone will see in a long time. The way how Future Diary commits to bringing entertainment than to explaining logic makes it stand out from the crowd. The fact that it does not bind itself to the usual structure of what to expect from fiction just makes it all the more so enjoyable. I definitely do hope that more people can appreciate and recognize it. \
And so, with that, I conclude the reasons of why do I think that Future Diary is quite a piece of \"art\", although definitely not one that everyone can appreciate equally.\
Let me touch on one more point before rounding this off. Some people have suggest that Future Diary as a satirical masterpiece, a deconstruction of the logic in story, magical girlfriend, deus ex machina etc. (to prevent spoiling) trope. Personally, this is not something that I will concur with, but seems interesting of an idea that I would brought it up, and would actually be a great explanation to everything that happened in this show. However, I still  prefer to keep my opinion of Future Diary as just a crazy batshit show without overthinking it too much, but hey, it's an interesting opinion. \
Some of my points may be indeed controversial here, but I do want to talk about my opinions of this show. Not everyone will enjoy this show, definitely, and even when on the same point, could have differing opinions. So, yeah, I kinda got what I wanted to talk about Future Diary here.\
Well, looks like I got side-tracked a little, pretty irresponsible...\
Damn.\
