    Overview:\
Mirai Nikki exploded on to the scene in 2011 and has built up quite the following. However, I have never liked this series and consider it one of the most overrated anime on this entire site! Mirai Nikki is one of those series that commits all the sins that other series get bashed for and somehow avoids any and all criticism. This is especially true on 4chan where Yuno has become something of a mascot and beloved icon. Although I almost admire the stubbornness and blind loyalty of its fanbase, I feel it is my duty to give this series the rich beating it deserves!\
Story\
          \
        and characters: 4/10\
Yuki is a very shy and introverted middle schooler that likes to talk to his imaginary friend, Deus ex Machina. One day he discovers that Deus is real and is in fact the God of this universe. However, God is getting old and needs a successor, so there is to be a Battle Royale to decide the heir. If no one wins than the apocalypse occurs. The bland and frankly awful main character Yuki quickly teams up with everyone's favorite yandare Yuno. Yuno for some reason has an obsessive love for Yuki and is willing to do anything to protect him. Why does she love him so much? No one knows. Yuno and Yuki go farther and farther into immoral territory and wish to win at all costs. Afterall, the winner can become God and simply bring back everyone that was killed. I won't spoil it, but the ending is one of the absolute stupidest endings I have ever seen! We should have seen this coming since the God is named Deus ex Machina, since no other words could describe how bullshit the ending was! What are my problems with the plot and characters? Firstly, Mirai Nikki doesn't simply homage other anime or adapt a subplot from a classic, but rather shamelessly steals from recent popular anime. It tries very hard to capture and emulate the cat and mouse games and high tension of Death Note, but fails because it isn't nearly as well written. This coming from someone who didn't even think Death Note was God tier writing in the first place. We have all seen the Battle Royale plot done a MILLION times before and written much better than the one in Mirai Nikki. We've seen the pink haired yandare girl gorily slaughter her way through dozens of people to get with bland male protagonist when it was Elfen Lied 7 years earlier in 2004. I could list other examples, but I don't want to write all day. The one thing I will give Nikki credit for is that it did do the sending text messages through time plot before Stein's Gate used it. The Mirai Nikki manga came out in 2006. Let's just face it, the characters fucking suck! The only character people like is Yuno, and she is honestly an extremely overrated character. Why? She kills without feeling or remorse and is a complete sociopath, yet we are supposed to like her. Her love for Yuki is completely unfounded and frankly doesn't make any sense. She has no real character depth and besides looking adorable killing people doesn't do anything to make anyone with a brain like her. We can't empathize with her, see into her head, or feel what she feels. Let's compare Yuno with her pink haired yandare predecessor Lucy from Elfen Lied. Lucy also has blind love for a fairly bland seeming protagonist, but she has a fucking reason to. He was the only person ever to treat her as a human being and show her kindness, after 10 years of encountering nothing but discrimination, fear, and hatred. Lucy kills plenty of innocent people, but feels deep remorse for these killings and realizes the gravity of her own crimes. Her feelings of guilt, psychological torment, and search for redemption makes the viewer actually able to empathize with her in a way that the viewer never can with Yuno. Keep in mind that  I'm not saying that being a sociopath = bad character. Johan Liebert of Monster is a sociopath, but is an amazing character. His bone chilling nihilism, mastery over manipulation and human emotion, and complete lack of reason for committing the crimes he does make him a terrifying pinnacle of human depravity and evil. Yuno is neither a great villian like Johan or a great anti-hero like Lucy. She is a very shallow yandare archetype that 4chan loves because lets face it, most of the people on /a/ are idiots and should GTFO my /b/! The final reason the plot is honestly pretty lousy is that it tries so hard to have the gore, rape, and darkness of a seinen(18 up demographic), but goes for the mindless happy ending of a shonen (12-17 demographic) where actions have no consequences and you can always just take a mulligan if you fuck up and did something you regret. Part  of what separates Shonen like Naruto and DBZ from Seinen like Monster and Elfen Lied is that if someone dies in a seinen series, they probably aren't going to be \"wished back\" next week. If a character makes a horrible mistake, that character has to live with it and doesn't simply get a do-over. Mirai Nikki is FAR too dark and depraved for a shonen but lacks the maturity, moral complexity, and intelligence of a good seinen. It enters into Tim Burton's Batman Returns territory where it is too dark for young kids and too stupid for adults.\
Art and sound: 7/10\
The art and sound are good, but not absolutely amazing and certainly not great enough to compensate for the shitty writing and characters. It looks good, but not revolutionary for its time period in 2006. The opening song is promising, but the overall OST is lackluster. \
Overall: 4/10\
To be fair, maybe I would feel different if I was younger and Mirai Nikki was my first dark and brutal anime. Maybe I would have been able to overlook its flaws like audiences did for early anime like Vampire Hunter D and Ninja Scroll simply because we were shocked and awed by what we were seeing. If you got something out of Mirai Nikki and found a strong moral, an empathetic character, thought provoking philosophy, or a bloody good time than good for you! I'm not going to condemn you and say that you are objectively wrong for liking this series. I will say that I personally hated this series and highly question if people are truly rating this series objectively and honestly. Of course there is no \"right\" and \"wrong\" when judging a subjective work of art, but it is my firm opinion that Mirai Nikki does NOT deserve a substantially higher rating than Elfen Lied and Angel Beats on MAL. It does NOT deserve to be ranked almost as high as Monster. I'm trying really hard to keep this review civil out of consideration for Mirai Nikki's many fans, but the fact it is rated above a 7 actually kind of pisses me off!\
