Mirai Nikki starts off about a socially awkward boy named Yukiteru Amano who uses his phone to make diary entries on the world around him, the people he notices etc. Being socially awkward, Yukiteru made friends in his mind. One being Mur Mur and the other being Deus Ex Machina (the God of Time and Space). During a conversation between Deus Ex Machina and Yukiteru,\
          \
        Deus makes Yukiteru's phone have future diary entries. So for example, when he finishes reading the future diary entry on his phone, the first thing it says is \"April 22, 6:59 [My Room] I hit a double bullseye at my morning dart throw. At first Yukiteru thinks he wrote all of this during his sleep, then later thinks it is all a coincidence. He is able to use his phone to know when their is an upcoming maths test and his phone has the answers to it. Anyway, to sum up the premises up for the rest of the series, Deus pits 12 random diary holders (just like Yukiteru) to play a game, where they have to kill each other. The last one standing's prize is being the successor to Deus Ex Machina of the God of Time and Space.\
Art - Bright colours, for a dark anime.\
Sound -  I like the sound of Mirai Nikki, this anime knows when to play the right type of music, being it suspensful or a happy tune.\
