Story: 9\
The story of Mirai Nikki is basically a survival game, you're given a diary that possesses a specific ability, maybe to see someones future? or to see what happens around you? The story is seen through the eyes\
          \
        of Yuki, a lonely kid that finds interest in writing what he sees around him in his diary. He believed to have two imaginary friends, Deus Ex Machina(the god of space and time) and Mur Mur, his servant. He was given a future diary, to see into the future, along with 11 other people, one of which including a friend from school Yuno(my favourite character of all time) who protects him because Yuki is a complete wimp.\
Now, I'll say for one, that this idea for the anime is really unique, that it was paced well, and had very strong points in terms of psychological breakdown and other things along those lines. I found episode 1 to be a bit slow, but then afterwards it just went from there, hits you with full force.\
The ending was a bit half-assed though, I'll say that now, which is one of the reasons why this aspect did not get a PERFECT RATING, however the story made it very much enjoyable and I enjoyed every part of it.\
Art: 10\
