 mirai nikki’s plot is a mess; it’s a haphazard conglomeration of elements that don’t work well together. the rape scenes were completely unnecessary, it has so many plot holes it might as well be swiss cheese, and the constant shifts in tone made it hard for me to take it seriously. ror example, in one episode, it had a happy scene that quickly escalated into a gory bloodbath. the whole scenario came from nowhere--and speaking of nowhere, nonsensical storylines and character arcs are constantly thrown into the mix, and they never end in satisfactory resolutions. worst of all, the core storyline of the show doesn’t make any sense when you look at it from another a clinical, logical perspective: prospective candidates to be the god of space and time can apparently be anyone, ranging from your eighty-year-old grandmother to a babbling five-year-old child. surely the current god could've chosen more appropriate participants? the entire process is a giant question mark that leaves room for more questions but fails to deliver answers. \
