    If you like emotional, gory, violent and slightly cliche anime, get ready for a ride on the feels train. \
Story 8/10: Mirai Nikki is your typical battle royal anime where everyone else must die for one person to live. It is a well used concept, and for many, it can be boring. I, on the other hand, find that it was very well executed and the fact that they had the future telling diaries gave it an interesting twist. Oh, and it also has a romance between a crazy woman and an always crying wimp. I wish I could give the story a higher rating,\
          \
        but from the middle of the anime and so on, the story becomes very messy and it feels like the anime is trying to be better than it is. I really liked the first half, and even though I enjoyed the second half too, it was a little hard to follow and kinda fell out of the interesting concept of the first half. \
Art: 8/10: The art was at some points really beautiful, but for the most part it was quite ordinary. The character design was good looking, the backgrounds were well made and the fighting scenes were intense, but it wasn't that much to brag about. What made me give the art a high rating was the openings and endings, especially the first opening. It's one of my all time favorites, with stunning and clever animation and music. It just gives me chills. The second opening is also good, but nothing in comparison. The endings are both decent and makes you anticipate the next episode. Even if you don't plan on watching the anime after this review, watch the first opening. You will not regret it! \
Sound 9/10; To start of I have to say, at first I didn't think the score for this anime stood out too much. Then I searched for some of the music online, and I instantly changed my mind. The music for the emotional scenes i stunningly beautiful, some are really depressing and the music makes the fighting scenes so much better. The op/ed music is also really good. It really shows the emotions this anime wants to show and makes you anticipate the the next episode and what's gonna happen. \
Character 8/10: I am one of the few people who absolutely loved Yuno and her yandere personality. I found it to be interesting and kinda lovable, and I just loved how deeply she cared for Yukiteru, even to the point where she could destroy everything for him to be happy. It was both pitiable and romantic. I also really liked a lot of the diary holders, especially Minene and her awesome personality. Sadly there was one character I just couldn't stand: Yukiteru. I just hated his whiny and wimpy personality, how he was so naive and always tried to do what he thought was good and ended up failing miserably at it. Even when he tried to look cool and actually succeeded at something, I just couldn't stand him. \
Enjoyment: 9/10: I really enjoyed watching this anime. It was exciting and intense, and held on to my interest until the very end. I even ended up reading the manga. Though it had a used concept, it managed to pull it off and keep me watching. That is what defines a good anime in my opinion. \
Overall 8/10: This show definitely has some flaws, but I feel that it makes up for it with emotional interactions and intense battles. It requires some patience to watch until the end and you can't have a thing against gore and blood, but this anime puts you on the feels train and won't let you off until the end station. If you prefer happy comedies and pure romances, this is not for you. But if you like crying your eyes out because of fictional characters, this will do the trick. \
