    I hate this show. It is without a doubt, one of the worst anime I have ever seen and I have no clue why people like it. Calling this show a travesty, a complete mess or an abomination would be too kind. BTW this review is going to be filled with spoilers from the show. Not that I'd ever encourage anyone to watch this...thing.\
But hey, I'll be fair. Let me start with the \
THINGS I LIKE:-\
(+)um...............it has a nice premise. Yeah, it's a battle royale with the players having the ability to read their future. Too bad the potential was squandered by the terrible writing\
          \
        but yeah, the premise is good.\
(+).......................................................oh yeah, in one of the episodes there is this white-haired gay dude who creates a strategy to defeat an opponent and this strategy makes sense. Too bad it's the only thing that makes sense in this entire \"series\" and the rules this strategy took into account for only mattered in that one episode, but yeah, that was there\
(+)and um...............................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................nope, that's it.\
So, thanks for reading my review, fans of Mirai Nikki, and please leave your wonderful, smart, positive, constructive criticism which........oh, to hell with it, I'm going to be killed anyways.\
THINGS I DON'T LIKE:-\
Everything else. I'll just get the animation and sound out of the way. They were the only decent things in this entire show. I did not find the animation to be anything great and I don't remember any of the songs apart from the first opening. I won't say I hated but I definitely did not like them. There was CGI in the show, and it looked terrible. Some of the animation was rather clunky. Some scenes with a lot of blood and gore had a very light colour palette which felt off. Character designs were alright except for a muffin lady who probably had it's origins on toilet paper. As for the sound, I've forgotten about it. Nothing else to say here.\
So apart from that, what is it that this show does so wrong?\
(-)The Premise\
So the start of the show is that there is this Shinji Ikari clone(albeit without the depth and struggles) who always writes has daily events on his cellphone like a diary and has an imaginary friend and one day he finds out that this imaginary friend of his is actually The God Of Time And Space and he has chosen twelve or thirteen or some number of people (including him) to fight a battle royale to the death where each of the participants' phones have the ability to show them text messages about what is going to happen to them in the future. So does that mean that every single one of them had to imagine Deus ex Machina(I'm not joking, that's the god's name....probably a symbolic representation for what the entire show is about) the exact same way? Seems kinda weird some of them would even have imaginary friends considering that even the police captain and the mayor of the city are involved. How are these guys selected? Are they chosen at random or does the god choose them? The reason I bring this up is because...\
(-)The Participants\
