    [174] = {
      score = 7,
      text = "                          \
    Yanderes... what is about them makes us love them, there insane, immoral, and downright creepy, and yet we still love them. Mirrai Nikki probably has the one yandere who is called the Queen of Yanderes, does she deserve this title and does this anime deserve the praise or hate it gets?\
Story 5/10: What started as a game set up by a dying god (how can a god die naturally), to choose his successor from a pool of 12 people, armed with cellphones that can see the future, turned into a plot so filled with holes it's like Swiss cheese. Originally what seems to be just\
          \
        about your average boring MC caught up in a thriller survival game, turns into this, 'what the hell', mess of time travel and dimension hopping. Honestly what seemed like a fairly straight forward plot turns into such a mess that it just leaves a bad taste in your mouth and your brain confused.\
Art 7/10: It's decent enough art, nothing to write home about but it certainty gets the job done. All the characters look good (well the females at least :P). The backgrounds and sets are all well animated and the effects are pretty good.\
Sound 9/10: That first opening theme... need I say more! It's probably my favorite anime opening and it just really sets the stage for epicness. The second opening theme, not the same just not the same, really disappointing. Still that first theme, utterly epic!\
Character 6/10: We have great characters, we have 'meh, characters, and then we 'ugh why' characters! Let's look at our mains, first we have Yuki, boring loner with no friends. Yeah because that's just what we want in an MC! He does become more of a badass towards the end, but it just feels really forced and I don't know it doesn't feel right. Now let's look at the real star of the show, Yuno. She is the embodiment of the Yandere! Crazy, in love, and no qualms about killing. Yuno is a great character, she has a tragic past, she's entertaining, and unless you hate Yanderes, you can't help but emphasize with her a little. Well the rest of the cast is varied, one diary user, 9th, Miene, is intersting. I love badass females but then they went and ruined her by turning her into a Tsundere. Other then that the other characters are either vary between okay and ugh. Akise, Hinata, and Mao are 3 characters that become Yuki's friends, really wish they had been developed more.\
Enjoyment 8/10: I feel like people often forget why we watch anime, not for a deep story, or nice art, or even great characters. We watch anime to be entertained! Despite all its flaws, Mirrai Nikki will have you entertained, it keeps you guessing on what's going to happen and wants you keep wanting more. It's fun to watch, just don't think to much on its many problems and you'll have fun.\
Overall 7/10: So does Mirrai Nikki deserve it's praise or it's hate? Well perhaps it's no masterpiece buts it's not garbage. All I can say it's fun, it has it flaws most certainly but it's fun and I feel like that's what matters. \
