                          \
    Despite my rating, The Future Diary is not without its flaws.  There's definitely some weird occurrences and outcomes of events.  I just personally find them plausible since it is a battle royale (survival) style anime and when something is a survival game, you tend to expect weird inexplicable things to happen.\
I was hooked from the first episode and for me, the show stayed very entertaining throughout the series.  It doesn't really become some deep adult story, but it also doesn't try to be deep when it's really not; I see it this way anyway.  I personally enjoyed all the additions to\
          \
        the plot in second half.\
To me, the characters were also really fitting for the show.  Ina survival game, you need a bunch of psychopaths to keep things interesting.  If everyone besides Yukiteru was also pretty normal, it wouldn't be as much fun to watch.  For how screwed up and over the top Yuno is, she is a perfect fit for this of story.  The rest of the cast were prettying interesting to when they had their screen time or at least they added interesting plot.  \
The music was really good too.  The opening theme for the first half instantly became one of my favorites and I don't think I ever skipped the first ending theme besides in the first 4 episodes that I saw at an anime club meeting.  The opening and ending themes for the second half are good too and also some of my favorites.  \
Overall, I feel very satisfied; I know many others are not satisfied with this, but I don't need to share their feelings.  I'm glad I suggested this when my anime club was voting on a thriller anime.  It was great watch and since I put it up without seeing it previously, it made for an even better experience.   \
