                          \
    Reading the other reviews on here, I can't help but feel they are a little harsh. I personally adored this show with a burning passion. I am a film major, so I've studied story and writing a few years now. Don't know if that strengthens my reasoning behind this review or not, but here it is nonetheless:\
Future Diary is a constant thrill ride. It contains lovable characters (yes, even the antagonists), drama on every corner, and a mind-blowing story. It starts off simple, they have these phones that tell their future. But from there on, things take a wide and drastic turn. Again, I pretty\
          \
        much liked every single character, and I don't know if I could even pick a favorite or not. We'll start off talking about Yuno though: she's adorable, right? She's likable, she's cute, and she's also a cold-blooded psychopathic murderer. But we still love her. Why? Good story writing, that's why. Though at first, viewers may be mildly annoyed by her stereotypical display of obsessive girl liking a boy, we quickly learn the concept is so much more beyond that. Yuno is NEVER the damsel in distress, she is a hardcore future diary game player with a dark past and even darker future. Everything she does, she does for the idea of love. She goes through such extreme measures simply because, she cannot handle a world without her true love. It's actually pretty simple when thinking of it in this sense, yes? We've all seen the unthinkable happen when it comes to love and passion right? Now take that unthinkable and TRIPLE it. It really masters the ability to make viewers wonder, would I do all this for the person I love the most? Do I support these actions being taken? Do I sympathize with these characters or do I despise them? It makes your brain whirl, and that's what I love about this show the most. On the surface, this show is so simple, but underneath, it contains so much depth and intricacy it's hard to even comprehend, let alone write a review about. One of my other most beloved characters in this show is Minene. She easily has the biggest character arc, and the most spunk. She starts off as our number one antagonist, by by the end, is one of our dearest friends. We see her life and her values take big shifts and we see her grow in such a beautiful way. And of course I should probably go ahead and talk about Yuki, right? Our big number 1 protagonist. Us viewers feel to be in the exact same position as him at all times. Never once do you get a chance to think \"what the hell Yuki? Are you insane?\" Because just like him, we really never KNOW what the right choice is. We are just as confused and perplexed as he is the entire time. It makes for a much more exciting ride too, I must say. And more entertaining as well. The only negative thing I think I could even say about this show is on Deus Ex Machina himself. The idea of him is well, of course... a deus ex machina? He literally just appears and the future diary game appears. Get it?  And while the concept of that is incredibly intriguing, it was a little hard for me to follow at some points. That, and the never-ending adorableness of MurMur. Hopefully I didn't spoil too much here. Moral of the review: give this show a shot. It gives you way more than you could ever expect. I think it's easily one of the best animes (and shows in general) that I have ever seen. \
