    Mirai Nikki was dreadful for me to watch, and I didn't enjoy anything from it at all. It had a potentially great story, only to be executed badly. Accompany that with ignorant annoying characters, nudity, multiple rape scenes, and failed comedy attempts to make me laugh, you have this anime. What redeems Mirai Nikki from getting a 2 from me however, is it's beautiful art and alright soundtrack.\
The story basically is, 12 people are given devices known as \"Future Diaries\", cellphones that have the ability to tell the future, predict movements, etc. Not only that, but they are chosen to participate in a death game\
          \
        where they all have to kill each other. Last person standing gains the position of God.\
From the outside view, I thought I would end up liking this anime. However, after 26 episodes, I was ultimately proven wrong.\
The biggest problem for me were the two main characters, Yuki Amano, a shut-in 8th grad boy that writes in his diary all day, and Yuno Gasai, another 8th grade girl with perfect marks in school. They both could be single-handedly the worst written characters that I have EVER seen. \
Yuki does absolutely nothing beneficial. His decision making skills are on point with Nigel Farage. Some of the things that Yuki has done are so stupid that it's actually mind boggling. What's strange is that he's paranoid and a complete wuss for about half of Mirai Nikki, and then the last couple episodes his personality does a full turn around, where he's comfortable knowing that he shot and killed three of his best friends. When he's in a fight, he is completely useless. The best thing I've seen him do is stab someone in the abdomen. That's it. Other than that, he leaves all the fighting to his unbelievably overpowered and strong lover, Yuno.\
Yuno is the Mary Sue of this anime. Although she may not be as annoying or bad as Yuki through understandable story telling, Yuno still makes absolutely no sense. She does all the fighting for Yuki, out of her love for him. Apparently, she has more combat experience than those in the military or police force, with no explanation. She might as well be completely invulnerable to anything and everything, except when someone touches Yuki. For example, for kissing him, you get your throat cut open. That's nice.\
Both these characters have so many episodes dedicated into developing their backstories, yet they still make no sense and end up leaving us with more questions. In fact, I liked the supporting characters more than the main ones. \
There will be spoilers in this paragraph. I will be talking about the story and the rest of the character cast. For me, the story was awkwardly painful. Many of the Future Diary Holders have no development. Take a look at a character named Bacchus. He is suddenly introduced and forced into the viewer's face as the anime begins to highlight him for the last couple of episodes. All we know is that Yuno and Yuki are on a mission to eliminate him and Eighth. Then it proceeds without telling us any information or why. I also need to mention that the story-telling is awful. They left me with so many unanswered questions that I cant count. By around 10 episodes in, I had stopped taking Mirai Nikki seriously. \
Thanks for reading.\
