    For every positive, ten negatives\
Mirai Nikki is a show with a not so great first episode, but promises to get better. All it does is go downhill. \
The plot is about a survival game to decide who will become the next god. Twelve players participate and each one of then have a future diary.\
The problem with this is that the potential of the diaries to resolve problems or be used smartly to win battles is totally lost. Most situations where the main characters are in danger or faced with a challenge are resolve by luck or a convenience, or even worse, plain dumbness of the\
          \
        characters. \
All the plot holes and continuity mistakes don't help either. When they happen so frequently its difficult to ignore them, and most of them are really avoidable.  This is lazy from the writers.\
