      text = "                          \
    Mirai Nikki is probably best known for its female lead Yuno Gasai, the prime example of a so called Yandere. But it also has an interesting premise: The God of Space & Time & Death is about to perish and wants to find a new god by giving 12 individuals the chance to use their cellphone diaries to look into the future and kill each other untill only one participant remains.\
Story:\
The idea of the story is nothing new, we have seen something similar in Battle Royale and other works, but the future diaries give it a fresh touch. We get to see different versions of\
          \
        the device, their strengths and weaknesses and the cleverness (or lack thereof) of their owners. The story itself never falls flat and provides constant conflict and action (which often moves into splatter territory).\
9/10\
Art:\
The animation looked solid at first, but as the show continued, it provided quite a few awkward animations. I don't know why this happened, because in the beginning it all went down smoothly. The CGI effects blend in well and don't disrupt at all (and that's coming from somebody who dislikes CGI in general). In fact later on, they look even better than the classic animation.\
6/10\
Sound:\
The first opening was one of the best I've seen yet and really set the mood for what you are about to watch. Sadly it got replaced midway by a not so cool song that is sung in Engrish. The ending was okay, not good but not bad either. The soundtrack didn't really stick to me, but it was never a disturbance or distraction, so I'd say it's solid.\
6/10\
Characters:\
Now here's the major problem of Mirai Nikki. The male lead has to be one of the worst characters I've ever seen. Many people despise him for being a wuss and they are kinda right. Yukiteru in itself is annoying as hell, but the combination with Yuno, who keeps exploiting him, could have worked well. But after she went too far and Yukiteru even WANTS to completely avoid her, he keeps coming back for more. That isn't excusable with his weak character anymore, that's just going back to status quo for the sakel of it. As if that wasn't enough, he becomes a complete bastard (who is still a wuss) and Yunos character takes some hits too. While she started out as a great villain, she was more and more devillified as the story progressed, making this show lacking an actual antagonist. The only thing saving this show at all are the minor characters, which are a lot of fun. The other diary owners, Akise, Deus & Mur Mur kept me entertained when the main characters failed to do so.\
3/10\
Enjoyment:\
