      text = "                          \
    STORY - 7\
ART - 7\
SOUND - 8\
CHARACTER - 7\
ENJOYMENT - 7\
Grossed out? Unsettled? Annoyed and frustrated? Even be saddened or delighted by some of the events that transpired? I would be lying if I said Mirai Nikki was an anime that didn't mold my feelings very frequently. Many good and bad factors played into all these changes that happened in me during my time watching the show.\
Introducing diaries that can predict the future in a multitude of ways set up a great, branching storyline for the plot. In essence, it's a bloody survival game bringing out the disturbing sides of our species. All seems well\
          \
        but there were flaws that I have to point out despite this creative foundation. Before I get to that, the anime diverged from others because of the heavy focus on a lot of complex matters that linked strongly with the ideas of morality and unlawfulness. Murder, psychopath, justice and deception are some to name a few. My fascination did peaked during all the related discussions. These traits were molded within the characters who have experienced tragic backstories, developing not only their nature and personality but also promoting their survival in the game. Distinctiveness made way for unique strategies in which they face death at each turn, however, a couple of the battles lacked excitement and tension as they were contrived. Same with finding myself disappointed by the build up of many characters, only to get paid off by some undeserving or abrupt conclusion. In spite of this, some were treated well though. Another side of focus that was really intriguing was the questionable relationship of 'love' between the two main characters, a weak lonely boy with a crazy yandere girl. While they did get annoying on occasions, they served as a controversial mystery and topic that sprinkled more interest to the story.\
Adding to the discomfort from the main story was in how we see each characters in color. The most compelling aspect from the visual was in the sinister expressions of the characters, showing their bloodlust, violent temptation or madness. It also produced the more anxious atmosphere such as fear and panic. I find it to really get into your senses in a good way, watching them transform into something we don't see everyday. Color themes also contrasted between gory darkness for tension to relaxed brightness for a more peaceful setting. Similarly, the character designs felt fresh, especially in the use of the eye design. I loved its depictions throughout changing environments with an example of how it can be lifeless in more uneasy situations. As for the animation, it can get jarring and unrealistic at times during the fight scenes, being out of place to what I was expecting. But most of the time, the quality was quite average. Even though some of the voice-acting lacked emotions, the actors did a pretty good job generally. Using OSTs helped bring out some of the important factors that were lost from the lower quality in animation and voice-acting.\
So yeah, this thriller of survival game was a whole new experience to me. Its ideas were thought out brilliantly but it fell during the execution and just made certain parts of the plot weak. Contrary to this, the last several episodes of Mirai Nikki were thankfully executed with a great approach, concluding to a strong finish.",
