      text = "\
                          \
    I'm gonna be honest, it is tough for me to review this and to justify my scores. Because I'm gonna start with talking about the enjoyment which I give a 10 here and that's because I absolutely adore this show, I watched it 5 times and I enjoyed myself every single time from the beginning until the end. \
And yet the show is FILLED with flaws. It's got it all, inconsistent story quality, inconsistent character personalities, inconsistent art quality and some pretty damn big logical issues with the story.\
The only part of the anime that in my opinion is actually flawless is the sound, the\
          \
        voices fit the characters and the music is amazing (anyone would agree that the first opening is one of the best openings ever).\
Now onto the flaws...\
The art is weird. Some characters have really good designs that stand out in a good way while some others look like parodies making the show lose what is supposed to be a dark atmosphere. Almost everyone looks quite realistic and then you got this cook who's 3 feet tall, has a head that's actually larger than its whole body and keeps walking as if she had paralyzed arms ; there is no reason for that character to look that way, it's just stupid and inconsistent.\
Then when it comes to animation it's relatively impressive ; the animations themselves sometimes feel slightly poorly made but they're at least always very smooth and they're never straight up bad.\
The story now....The idea of the story is great, the execution is lacking. The whole concept of \"you need to beat your rivals using your diaries\" almost gets forgotten at times and instead everything gets solved by pure violence when you'd really expect people trying to outwit each other using their diaries. The diaries also have another issue : a lot of them are similar to each other or feel like they don't do anything. In the end the only 2 diaries that actually get used often and properly are yuki's and yuno's but that's to be expected.\
Another big problem of the story is that a lot of events feel like they got no consequence at all. People get killed all around and it barely makes the news ; someone gets knocked out while yuno and yuki try to kill a diary owner in that person's house and when the person wakes up she doesn't ask any question and keeps going on with her life. Those are only 2 examples of loopholes but the story has got a fair bit more of those unfortunately.\
On the plus die, the anime manages to stay overall quite dark as it should be. And not just murder and creepy psychopathic girlfriend dark, we're talking 14 year old girl gets raped dark. Although at times the anime just tries to be funny by making an extremely ridiculous and out of place scene that's supposed to make you laugh but when it happens between the murder of 20 people, a young girl losing her arm and another one about to get raped, you don't want to have a funny break you just want to stay immersed in that dark story and see how it ends.\
The characters...There's just so much to say but to say it simply : if Mirai Nikki was a game of League of Legends, Gasai Yuno would be solo carrying the team while everyone else fed the entire game.\
So in case the game analogy doesn't help you I'm gonna say a bit more : Yuno is about 80% of the reason I love the anime. Every other character is either completely stupidly written or makes at least one gigantic nonsensical decision at the worst possible moment. I really can't go into depths about it without spoiling the entire show but if there is one thing you need to remember it's this : if you don't like yanderes then don't watch the anime, if you can't even enjoy yuno you will not like the show at all.\
So yeah, a lot of flaws, I almost entirely wrote about this show negatively and yet I still stand by my point : this anime is my favorite anime I ever watched. And yes it's a totally biased and unreasonable statement. I love Yuno's yandere personality and I love the Yuno x Yuki couple. And yet I know that it shouldn't be enough for me to love the show like that. I really liked Lucy in Elfenlied as well yet I wouldn't watch Elfenlied again because just liking one character isn't enough for me to enjoy an entire anime. And yet for Mirai Nikki it works, somehow and I can't explain to you why.\
So it's really up to you. Mirai Nikki is a very polarizing anime. And you will find a lot of people tell you it's the best thing ever and a lot of other people will tell you it's one of the worst anime ever. I'm not either of those people and honestly the best way for you to figure out if you'll like it or not in this case is to just watch the first 2 episodes. If by the end of episode 2 you feel neutral about Yuno, it probably won't be worth watching the rest of the show.\
