    Which do you love more: the journey or the destination?\
I ask \"more\" because, as we all know, both parts are essential to a show. The beginning, the middle, and the end are what make a story.\
In the case of Mirai Nikki, however, you won't get a perfect story precisely because you won't get a perfect beginning, middle, and end.\
So I ask: do you love the journey more or the destination?\
I won't spoil anything except one unfortunate fact, which is better for you to know regardless: the ending is not fully satisfying.\
To be specific, the show is 26 episodes plus a conclusion OVA called \"Mirai Nikki\
          \
        Redial.\" Redial is the official ending; watch it after the first 26 episodes. It is conclusive; it does wrap up the series; but it's not fulfilling. It does provide answers; but it does not really give satisfactory ones.\
In short: the ending is merely mediocre.\
However, the beginning and the early middle are glorious. The late middle slowly descends into the mediocrity of the ending.\
Hence, I gave the story a 6. The beginning half was fantastic and sits at close to an 8; the latter half lurked down to a 5 or so.\
The art was good. Nothing mind-blowing, but still good.\
The music....\
Oh my goodness. The music.\
The first OP is just brilliant. It's the only thing from the show I continue to rewatch. It showcases the essence of what the show's ideal state of being was. It's excellent. Please give the OP a try, even if not the show.\
The characters are great as well, in particular Gasai Yuno. This show is really about her and her interaction and relationship with the MC. She's the reason I watched the show, to be honest.\
Hence, I enjoyed the show very much. Even with a lackluster ending, I liked it overall.\
Hence, I give it a Good score. If you like thrillers and Yuno's character, and if the OP gives you the good kind of shivers, watch the show. You'll enjoy it.\
