    [311] = {
      score = 9,
      text = "\
                          \
    Overview:\
\"This is insanity. There's just no other word for it.\"\
Actually, \"Mirai Nikki\" can be described using many words- insane, bonkers, violent, twisted, shocking, strange, odd, weird.... and I'd say there are many more words along those lines that can be used to sum up this series. Simply put, this is one of the craziest anime I have yet to see. The characters are larger than life, the action is fast and suspenseful, the story is absolutely crazy, set pieces are brilliantly creative and the series throughout is pretty damn enjoyable.\
Story (9/10):\
That line above comes from our male protagonist Yukiteru Amano, a shy, introverted young boy\
          \
        who spends almost all his time writing a diary in his cellphone and talking to his imaginary friend, Deus Ex Machina, the God of Space and Time. However, he soon discovers that Deus isn't as imaginary as he once thought and that he, having been granted the ability to see the future through his diary, is one of 12 chosen candidates to inherit the Throne of Time as Deus is going to die soon and needs a successor. These people are forced to compete in a Survival Game where they have to hunt down and kill each other and the last man standing will become the next God.\
Now, Yuki is completely blown away by the whole thing, and not in a good way, having no desire to win. Unfortunately for him, he is Deus's favourite to win, and therefore the primary target of all the other Diary Users. He needs help, and thankfully he gets some in the form of the main female protagonist, Yuno Gasai. The catch is that this girl is a seriously unstable psychopath who has been stalking him for a year and has an obsessive crush on him, to the point that she's willing to kill anyone who could possibly get in the way of the two of them being together.\
The amount of suspense in this series is colossal, as any person who gets close to Yuki could potentially be trying to kill him, which makes Yuno, whether he likes or not, the only person he can truly count on. There's also a huge number of twists as well, though some may be a bit too crazy for some people. There are also occasional moments where the fast pacing breaks, having some really comical parts after a really disturbing episode, which may and have put off some people. If you can get past these, however, you will be rewarded with a brilliant, unique story that will leave you guessing to the very end.\
Art & Animation (8.5/10):\
Visually, \"Mirai Nikki\" looks very good. While there are certainly better looking anime in this decade, all the characters are well-drawn and things always run very smoothly. Special mention has got to go to Deus, who despite being a tower-high CGI-esque being still manages to fit brilliantly with the rest of the animation. The effects when the Future Diaries rewrite themselves are really good as well, among other things.\
Sound & Dialogue (9.5/10):\
\"Mirai Nikki\"'s soundtrack isn't the best around, but it still gets the job done and really fits the tone of the show. The opening and ending themes are brilliant, especially the ending themes. The voice acting is really good as well. Even those who didn't like the dub still agree that Kent Williams' performance as Deus is godly (no pun intended), and I'm one who really liked the dub. Brina Palencia does an awesome job as Yuno, being able to switch her voice from normal to psychotic within seconds. If anything, she sure knows how to pull off an angry scream. Josh Grelle also has an impressive range as Yukiteru. I especially liked his calm voice, which really fitted Yuki in the latter half of the series.\
Characters (9/10):\
\"Mirai Nikki\" has a brilliant cast of characters, which is saying something considering about 90% of them are villains. Yukiteru tends to be a very controversial character among fans. There are some who hate him for being weak and cowardly, while there are others who consider him a relatable and sympathetic character who reacts realistically to the situation he's been pulled into. I agree with the latter party. I mean, try being a socially awkward 14-year-old boy who is forced to compete in a deathmatch filled with psychopaths. And the only person you can trust is the crazy Yandere who is insanely in love with you for reasons you can't figure out. He most certainly grows a spine as well and the badass upgrade is absolutely awesome.\
You know this is a messed up world when the crazy stalker is one of the more sympathetic characters. Honestly, you sometimes think that it's actually the world that's insane rather than Yuno. Compared to the actual villains in the series, Yuno really isn't that bad, as she's one of the few characters looking out for anyone other than herself. Therefore, I consider her an anti-hero, if a very, very dark one. That may seem hard to believe considering some of the things she does, but believe me when I say she has a very good reason for her obsession with Yukiteru. She has a truly horrible past and when you learn it, you will be screaming at Yuki for him to give her a hug. Also believe me when I say that, however, obsessive it may be, her love for Yuki is genuine. She's many things, but she's not a hypocrite. Besides that, she manages to be both really cute and really scary, often at the exact same time! Seriously, I don't know how they managed to pull that off but they did and the results are captivating. In short, she is a really compelling, unpredictable and truly awesome character and not only is she my favourite character in the series by far, she's one of my favourite anime characters, full stop, which is saying a lot as I usually don't like psychopaths at all. Then again, I guess that just goes to show how unique she is.\
It's hard to talk about the other characters without spoiling something but I will say that they are very good with a few exceptions. I will say, however, that the Diaries' abilities serve as a reflection of the personalities of their owners. Yuki's Diary, for example, tells him everything about his whereabouts but nothing about what happens to him, while Yuno's Diary keeps her updated on whatever Yuki's doing 24/7, essentially making it the ultimate staking tool. This adds another layer to the suspense, as Yuki and Yuno must not only figure out who the other Diary Users are, but also what aspect of the future their Diaries hold in order to defeat them.\
Another interesting aspect is that the show also goes out of its way to show just how unfit some people are to be parents, as nearly all of the characters are or were forced to deal with some kind of abuse or abandonment by the people who were supposed to be taking care of them. The best parents seem to be the ones who died before they could turn into horrible people. This does a brilliant job at developing the various characters and teaches us a sad yet valuable lesson about life.\
Enjoyment (9.5/10):\
\"Mirai Nikki\" had me on the edge of my seat from start to finish. It never stopped trying to shock me to the point that I hardly had any breath in my lungs. And I love it for that. It never got to the point of being predictable and I was always ready for more. To be really satisfied, however, you will have to watch the OVA, \"Mirai Nikki: Redial\", as the anime itself unfortunately has a pretty ambiguous ending that will only make sense if you watch the OVA. Some may also find the concept to be too ridiculous so if you don't like anime, you probably won't like this. If you manage to make it through the first time, however, it is definitely worth watching a second time as it casts multiple characters in a different light and you can learn things you may have missed the first time around.\
Overall:\
This is an absolutely awesome series and I am proud to say I had a fantastic time watching it. It's an absurd, unique and highly suspenseful roller-coaster ride that will keep you wondering what the hell is going on and your patience will almost certainly be rewarded. If nothing else, you should at least watch it for its tragic, badass and oh so adorable Yandere Queen. If you're looking for something that will blow your mind, look no further than \"Mirai Nikki\".\
Score:\
9+8.5+9.5+9+9.5=45.5/50=9.1/10\
