    This anime does one thing so incredibly well that, while it does have a ton of faults, the show is still very good and well worth a watch.\
As far as this show goes there's very little I can say without spoiling it so this review will likely be a little short.  The best part of this show is, by far, the way they absolutely nailed their portrayal of the stalker character Yuno.\
Good god I've never had an anime freak me out before but...  This chick is terrifying!  She goes from one extreme to the other so quickly that it makes your head\
          \
        spin.  Also the animation they give for her, especially her eyes, is so absolutely spot on that the entire show could ride on it to success.  Some would argue that it does; and I'd be lying if I said I didn't agree with that to a point.\
The story is a classic example of great intentions with great delivery... until (The Fire Nation Attacked!) disaster strikes.  At first I though of it as a genre breakdown with Deadman Wonderland aspirations in regard to the blood and gore.  But then they go and try to make certain characters lovable and suddenly plot holes start appearing and by the end the show is more confusing than anything else.  But that doesn't mean it wasn't a fun ride downward.\
As weird as this sounds, this didn't hamper my enjoyment of the show.  The characters are all very well done which makes the plot holes seem a lot less of a problem than one would think.  However if a plot hole immediately ruins a show for you you are going to struggle with this anime.\
The animation, especially the opening opening, is quite good with a couple really high points.  If you don't ever want to watch this show the opening is still well worth a watch.  It tells everything and nothing, the music is great.  And the animation is fantastic!  Moving on.\
