        is too weird to hang out with because all he does his type his diary in his cellphone. He speaks to no one but his imaginary friend, Deus. But things got weird when Deus turned out to be real.. everything was turned upside down. He was able to meet friends, allies and enemies; to be able to feel love, loss, and betrayal.\
This anime is about struggling to survive, with the help of the Future Diaries, and who will inherit the title \"god\". \"Mirai Nikki\" is covered with all sorts of emotions-- fear, happiness, excitement, sadness. But at its very core, this anime revolves around love.. Of how one's willpower can change the future. And even as you go nearer to the ending, all things were for the reason of love.. or is it obsession? \
Yuno Gasai is the spice of the story. Her twisted thinking made the anime more interesting and worthwhile. Her obsession for Yukiteru makes you guess if she'll really protect him or kill him at the end. You may ask of how can Yukkii trust her so much despite of her shady personality and past. But if we were in Yukkii's shoes, Yukkii really doesn't have much of a choice. The only way he sees to survive is to stick with Yuno. \
The overly-attached-girlfriend personality of Yuno is so creepy that you'll get annoyed yet love her at the same time. Well, that what makes her \"Yuno\" after all. Her insanity reaches to the point where you can no longer see what she's thinking.. her mind is sooo twisted. And that makes the story exciting and full of mystery.\
The thing about this anime is that it'll make you think of the possible ending. 1. Yukiteru will win and Yuno will be loyal and die (because we all know that Yukiteru is so much for a good guy) 2. Yuno will betray Yukiteru and inherit the title \"god\" 3. Both of them will die (it's either they'll commit double suicide, or the world will end since none of them became the winner). But you'll be really surprised of how things ended, no jokes. This anime is full of surprises (though some things were a little bit off and too much).\
The art of this anime was quite amazing. Nothing was rushed and shabby. Everything compliments the scenario-- if it's action, flashback, sad scenes etc. Even the backgrounds and landscapes were so detailed. I find the art smooth and beautiful. I salute the artist/s!\
