    Frankly, I didn't start watching this anime, even then I read synopsis and reviews, but I'm really glad that one day I thought \"Why not?\". I'm not the fan of thrillers, but this anime still was able to hold my attention for several days. If there wasn't the study in university, I would watch it in just one day, from morning to midnight. So why \"Mirai Nikki\" got under my skin? Well, there are several reasons.\
Synopsis gives basic understanding of story and seems like usual anime plot with idea of battle royale. The fight of twelve players for becoming new God of Time and Space\
          \
        has many tense moments because of their diaries, constantly predicting future. That only gives many advantages for developing story. And trust me, they are properly used.  Furthermore, there are some questions about Deus Ex Machina and the diaries. All that helped story to hold interest with grip of steel.\
But story not only revolves around battles, there is still place for characters with their peculiarities. Characters not just actors playing their fixed roles, they are able to go beyond archetypes if there is a serious reason. There are enough situations that force they to go against own opinion, but this has some consequences and affects on their personality. But the most interesting is different levels and types of insanity amongst characters, which make story twists really unexpected and tense. You will be stunned by some actions of characters, but you still will be able to understand their reasons. That is my main point of interest in this anime.\
You may ask, “So why not 10 for story and characters?”. Well, that’s more subjective matter. If you like psychological thrillers, then just think that I ranked everything by ten. But I judged this anime independently of it genre and didn’t paid attention to specifics of “psychological thrillers”. I don’t like completely dark atmospheres, where is no place for happiness without pain. After “Mirai Nikki” I was in bad mood and hopefully it didn’t last long. But nevertheless, minus one point for that.\
Music is very good and completely matches the scenes, without making phony tension. Mix of electronics with some classis elements and even Eastern motives. Some even made their way to my playlist. But this is true about music in episodes, not opening and ending.\
Frankly, I’m not the type, watching anime because of art, but I haven’t seen any mistakes or can blame “Mirai Nikki” for bad visual style.\
