    [403] = {
      score = 6,
      text = "                          \
    Back when I first heard of Mirai nikki, I thought of it as a Death Note rip-off, but good news, I was wrong. But this was also bad, because a rip-off of a masterpiece could, in my opinion, only be good. But I was wrong. \
Let's get on this review of the masterpiece that could have been, Mirai Nikki, loved by most, hated by the others.\
Story 5/10 \
When I began watching this show, I could only marvel at the story: it was so good, a little rushed at times, but it was so good ! Soon, I saw that I my mistake. Starting from around\
          \
        the 8th episode, the plotholes began to appear, and the villain-of-the-week schema had begun. And so, the psychological thriller that I loved so much at first turned into a mainstream shounen battle anime by the last episodes. It looks like the guys who made this anime had a very talented staff for the beginning of the show, and suddenly fired them to replace them with a bunch of amateurs. \
Art 8/10\
Art-wise, there's nothing, or almost, to say. The animation is decent, and beautiful during some of the battle-scenes. It's not a masterpiece, but beautiful nevertheless.\
Sound 9/10\
I loved Mirai Nikki's soundtrack before I even started watching it. Why ? Because of the masterpiece that is its first opening. But, as all openings go, it was replaced with something that I hate in animes : a song sung in English by a Japanese singer. The Japanese accent destroys all that could have made the song great, in my opinion. On the other hand, both the endings are great. The OST is not bad either.\
Character 5/10\
Here's the tricky part. If there's one thing that Mirai Nikki is loved for, it's the characters, especially Gasai Yuno, the queen of all yanderes. But that's what I hate about her. You can resume all of her thinking in one sentence : she loves the main character, Yukiteru, and will do everything for him. Of course, there's the final plotwist,  which could have made the character incredibly better. But it didn't. \
Now, let's move to the main, Amano Yukiteru. During all the show, I waited for him to finally do something, stop hiding behind Yuno, becoming badass, I don't know.  The only character who's written more badly than this guy is Yuno. He's annoying most of the time, and, like the rest of the cast (except Yuno, the only intelligent character), he's TOTALLY STUPID.\
The other diary owners are even worse. Their development barely grazed the surface, they were stupid as hell, and sometimes defied logic, only contributing to make more plotholes. \
Let me explain. Some of them appear to know Deus. How did they meet him ? We don't know. How did a 5-year-old girl got her hands on highly dangerous gas ? We don't know. I could go on for a long time like this, but I don't want to totally spoil the story.\
Enjoyment 6/10\
I mildly enjoyed this anime. Some moments felt boring, while others were absolutely great. The suspense was often killed by comic relief moments in the middle of a fight, and the writing kept getting worse as time went by. \
Overall 6/10\
If I had to put it shortly, I'd say Mirai Nikki was a huge disappointment. It had huge potential, but didn't manage to exploit it. \
Trust me I'd like to recommend it to you, but I can't. Don't watch this anime. It'll only be a boring and disappointing experience.\
Thanks for reading this review, and if you want to discuss about this anime, don't hesitate to message me !",
