      text = "\
                          \
    Since Mirai Nikki is the first anime I've watched from the thriller genre, I honestly didn't know what to expect. After watching the first episode, I was really creeped out, but each episode made me want to watch the next. Even if you don't normally go for dark-themed anime (like me), I would definitely suggest that you give this one a shot.\
[Story: 9]\
The story was good and the pacing was just right. There were some things that could've been explained better, but if you're not as observant as others, you'd hardly notice them. There was a lot of romance and definitely a good amount of\
          \
        action. The first episode was really intense, but the badass ending really topped it.\
[Art: 9]\
I really liked the art and how all the characters looked (well, maybe Yuki's character is an exception--not really a fan of his character's physical appearance).\
[Sound: 10]\
You know how in horror films, the sound effects are sometimes scarier than the other scenes, or when they boost the scare-factor of the overall film? I think that's how it was with Mirai Nikki, for me.\
[Characters: 7]\
I would love to get into each character and what I love about them, but that might take some time. Generally, I loved all the characters (especially Yuno!) except for Yuki, our male lead. I guess you could say he's practically a male version of Bella Swan. (I'm not bashing Twilight--I actually like it--but we all know that Bella doesn't do anything to help.) Yuno, the female lead, is a character you could either love or hate. I definitely loved her. I thought her character was the best developed out of them all.\
[Enjoyment: 10]\
Like I said, each episode made me want to watch the next! Most of the time, when I watch anime, I end up getting bored as the series goes on... Mirai Nikki doesn't drag the plot around, every episode has a purpose, and every episode is thrilling.\
[Overall: 9]\
        ",
      helpful = 3,
    },
    [413] = {
      score = 6,
      text = "                          \
    Mirai nikki also known in english as future diary is a 26 episode long series that is about a select few number of people battling each other in a battle royal deathmatch orchestrated by the god of the world deus ex machina. This show is really nothing special despite it having a glimmer of hope in the first few episodes with adding a very original concept of having a specific diary that can tell the future in various ways but all balanced which personally i believed based on setting alone was an anime brilliant enough to rival things such as Fate/zero. \
However, sadly this show\
          \
        had an ultimate downfall of making this show a more character driven story which failed as all the characters except gasai Yuno was completely one dimensional an example would be Yuki who is a Shinji hikari type character who is really annoying but unlike Shinji never developes. The show would mainly revolve between the romance of Yuno and Yuki making the show 90% of the time a nightmare to watch due to the actions made by yuki. So why would my enjoyment of this show be an 8/10? because that final 10% is close to being extremely satisfying not only knowing that this discusting monstrosity of a psychological thriller anime was nearly over and the last minute of the anime before the ending credits was brilliant and emotionally compelling. This is a perfect example of why i believe a show can be good if it just has a great ending. However all i can give this show is a 6/10 because instead of being a spectacle in its own right it uses very stereo typical plot devices etc. that are nothing even remotely unique. It was executed soo poorly that it was depressing to watch it could have been an epic that focussed around the battle royal and character motivations of all rounded development but instead introduced side characters that i didn't even in the slightest care about. Also the show revolved an anxious romance between 14 year olds which felt very awkward especially where i was supposed to use my brain to watch because the last time i recall it psychological thrillers require use of a brain. So besides one interesting character, a brilliant ending and an original concept mirai nikki is nothing special instead of watching this i would recommend something in my opinion is way better of the same genres just instead of romance there is mystery and instead of that multi world BS which i saw as nothing more than a plot device there are actual explanations to what happens only if the two seasons are completed. The show is higurashi no naku koro ni  this is my first ever review and i hopped you found it useful in your ultimate decision to the show\
        ",
