    [Okay, so this is my first time writing a review so please bear with me xD ]\
Spoilers are present!!\
Scrolling down my facebook news feed, I've seen pictures of a pink haired girl who looked adorable and at some point she looked completely creepy! which i found very odd. So, when I looked up what anime it was, I stumbled upon the tittle 'Mirai Nikki' . Before watching it, I collected information and read a few details that left me dumb founded. And the curious child inside me made me watch the whole episode only in a day.\
After a few episodes, I told myself that I've\
          \
        understood the blot and the ending is really predictable. Yukiteru and Yuno will eventually kill all the other diary owners, Yuki will kill Yuno and Yuki will become god. And possibly a press of a button will bring Yuno back to life and they will live a happy life. But I was wrong, I have never been so wrong in my whole life! \
STORY 8- The story itself is really impressive. Considering all the twists here and there. There were some parts where the characters seems pretty calm  and laid back after a big disaster happened, and I personally disliked that--they acted as if nothing bad just occurred.\
But I have to applause all the diary owner's story, each individual had a unique and touching story which i love very much. Though it's genre doesn't cover comedy, there were a lot of parts were in i laughed my ass off. 'm giving Mirai Nikki's story a 9 and not a perfect 10 because there were moments as if you feel lost, wondering if you skipped an episode or not. It's story was fast and I admit I hardly kept up with the pace. During episode 18 and above was a bit over the top and made me wonder if i'm still watching the same anime. Though, I really liked the idea of having a future diary :D\
