      text = "                          \
    I love-loved this series! The emotional hooks sunk in deep and I bought it immediately afterwards with no regrets \
Mirai Nikki revolves around Middle-School student Yukiteru, a social recluse, and the \"Survival Game\" he ends up participating in. With the help of a unique \"Future Diary\" Yuki must outsmart the other eleven diary owners to achieve the crown of \"God.\"\
I felt the pacing of events was great, but hiccuped at points, seeming to accelerate and brake to simulate a bit of whiplash for the viewer. Mostly because some characters are lovingly explored while others that are just as important fall by the wayside. Overall though\
          \
        it was enjoyable experience of twists and turns, with the last few episodes introducing a remarkable departure. \
The animation was good, without helping or hindering the series in any substantial way at any point in time.  \
The sound was well-done, though none of the music sticks out. The openings were catchy and enjoyable. I much preferred the sub voices over the dub, I felt that they better represented the characters...\
...which are strong and diverse! As speculation might hold, Yuno is a personal favorite of mine, and I found watching her to be an absolute treat. The main lead can occasionally become overly whinny and maudlin, but this is usually understandable if taken into the context of his character. Otherwise the supporting cast is fun and in many different shades. My other criticism is that some characters end up being thrown-away without much thought because of how little they were developed or had to offer. \
I enjoyed watching the series immensely, and look forward to the possibility of alternate plots and stories that I believe were recently announced!   \
        ",
