    So, I liked the character designs and the ideal that they weren’t super humanly powered battling one another. Having said that let’s focus on what I didn’t like. \
First, i want to state that I initially dropped this series after 12 episodes. It became clear that Yukiteru and Yuno would be the last two players in the game (that is NOT a spoiler it’s just common sense) and I did not care if they lived or died. Yukiteru is a terrible person and Yuno is worse. But I picked it back up, finished it and now I can conclude this is the second most overrated\
          \
        anime I’ve watched. Yukiteru becomes wishy washy over the whole homicide thing. Sometimes he’s crying and hollering how killing is wrong and takes drastic measures not to. Other times he gleefully commits murder with his own two hands. It doesn’t fit with him being partnered with the human homicide machine Yuno. Either you’re cool with murder or you’re not. One could even be on the fence about it or even feel one way about it then another. But no one switches back and forth on the matter. Yukiteru is a child, I’ll grant you that, but shouldn’t that put him at a huge disadvantage?  Yuno is his advantage, I’ll grant you that too. And the diaries and the manipulation of them are core to their survival. I just feel as though nearly every other diary user would have won this game. But Yuno’s homicidal devotion to Yukiteru got on my nerves. There’s nothing else to her character despite all her backstory. It’s just Yuki and kill. That got boring fast. Back to my first point, I counted four diary users (including Yuno) who simply didn’t kill Yukiteru because, well he’s the main character and it ruins the story if he dies. But that belittles the stakes of the game and the motivations of the other player. Kill 11 others to become god of the new world, what’s the hesitation or hold up? Deus Ex Machina indeed. Maybe I would’ve liked it more when it first came out or I was an adolescent with a grudge against the world, alors I am neither. It was entertaining and annoying at the same time. The end however seemed hokey and contrived when they literally could have had any ening they wanted. Plenty of better anime to watch out there.\
