    This is one of those series that I would only ever watch once. I liked some of the characters as characters, though i couldn't relate to a single one of them, i still enjoyed them as characters. The first half was great but the second half was horrid, which lead me to create an anime syndrome because I've noticed a trend with this series. And before I start, as will all of my reviews, there will be spoilers.\
Future Diary is about a teenage boy being thrust into a fight to become god against his will. There are 12 other people fighting to become god, some\
          \
        of them for selfish reasons such as the want of power or the ability to cause mass destruction and some for selfless reasons such as helping orphans or ridding the world of crime (yes that was 12's goal). The series revolves around this kid as he is forced, again against his will, to fight along side an insane woman named Yuno Gasai, who is quite literally the worst Yundere in all of anime, but more on her later.\
So time to talk about the massive upsides of this series, it's first half. In the first half we get Yukki putting up with the insane urges of Yuno and her delusions that he agreed to marry her, which he didn't, he said it jokingly 4 years before this series takes place. But we get a lot of good and realistic character interactions between Yukki and all of the other characters in this series, whether he is protecting them from Yuno or being protected by them he always reacts in a way that is realistic and entertaining to watch. And even finding out how each character's dairy worked (the blind man making recordings that talked about crime, the child with a picture diary that allowed him to see what would happen between meal times, and the scroll read by the Shinto Priestess with a horribly sad back story that tells her when people will arrive in her shrine). The first half of this series had a lot to off.\
But as i sit on my porcelain throne like a do when writing reviews I sit and think. Why have I been saying the first half this whole time instead of saying the entire series. Well I'll answer that now.\
This is going to be the first time that I am going to use the term anime syndrome in one of my reviews, because this seriously did start a trend with anime that I've noticed. The first half of this series was great, and if it weren't for the second half it would be on my favorites list. In the second half Yukki turns from a nice guy who actually cares about human life to a mass murdering, child murdering, psychopath. And he goes for Yuno, the person who kidnapped him and put him and tied him to a chair and force fed him soup after drugging him, saying she only wanted what was best for her. And in this part Yuno becomes more insane and literally kills everybody. She goes from an insane human being to a forced villain, who they then try and get you to sympathize with. And he ignores all of his friends who haven't actually lied to him and saved his life on numerous occasions. And the ending is shit, I mean that is the worst ending I have seen. It is a literal Deus ex Machina and i hate it. Though it wasn't as bad as some of other series's second halves. the next bad review is going to be alone the lines of online virtual reality video games that kill you.\
