          \
        the shocking or at times disgusting events are necessary for the character development. What makes the plot actually pretty great are the several twists and the unpredictability of the storyline. Whatever you think, you can be sure that the anime won't fail to surprise you. Also, the idea of the future diaries brings with it that you can expect some ingenious tactical moves. (Sorry for comparing again but I couldn't help to mention Death Note and Code Geass at this point. While they are mainly based on strategies, Mirai Nikki is more like a perfect mix between genres, including the one with a genius MC with supernatural abilities.)\
